HEADWORD: Cutgrass
<hw>Cut"grass`</hw> <pr>(k⟦ucr⟧t"gr⟦adot⟧s`)</pr>. <def>A grass with
leaves having edges furnished with very minute hooked prickles, which
form a cutting edge; one or more species of
<gen>Leersia</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

